\begin{document}$$ f_{{{\text{occurrence}}}} = \frac{{n_{{{\text{actual}}}} }} {{n_{{{\text{possible}}}} }} $$\end{document}where nactual is the number of times the contact occurs (with ambiguity taken into account), and npossible the total number of times this contact could occur between the relevant residues, either for all residues or only between ‘assigned’ residues. The occurrence is given in percent or as a fraction. The ‘ambiguity’ of an inter-atomic contact is defined as: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym} 
\usepackage{amsfonts} 
